</span><hr size=1> ::Shey began to breath deeply in pained strokes, but she didn't care much.  She wondered if Sartha was okay.  The one who hit her was an excellent shot, and Shey didn't think it was meant to kill.  With a sigh she took her clutched pendant and seperated it again, slowly she reacched over and put it in her pack,  hopeing it would be safe there, she alsop hoped, should she see hades after all, that sar would be the one to find it:: <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/usheyala.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sheyala</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_redspot.gif BORDER=0> at: 5/17/01 6:31:30 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#003366><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/usheyala.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sheyala</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_redspot.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>registered user</span><br>  Posts: 151<br> <font color=#FFFF33>(6/3/01 8:36 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=24.topic&index=56>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://geocities.com/Tokyo/Pagoda/8446/m-shead.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Holding on</span><hr size=1> ::With a growl, Shey snapped to a realization.  She was here lying, waiting for death, sure it would come, but what was she doing wasting her time lying down?  With a shake of her head she managed to stand.  Aphrodite hadn't spoken or said anything in a while, so Shey found her horse and began tracking down Sartha.  Her body hurt, and her mind swam like a dog in water, slow and clumsy, but still she kept going::<br>
<br>
&quot;Where did you all go?&quot;<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#336699><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uixlordhadesxi.showPublicProfile?language=EN>IX Lord Hades XI</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>registered user</span><br>  Posts: 37<br> <font color=#FFFF33>(6/3/01 11:45 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=24.topic&index=57>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> ::From the shadows::</span><hr size=1> ::Hades stepped out from behind one of the trees in front of Sheyala, as usual shadows seem to darken in his presence.  His hood drawn over his head, and his eyes of course hidden by shadow he gently put his forefinger to his lips as if almost to show a sign of being quiet.  He then remarked in a very hushed tone::<br>
<br>
&quot;You know, you really should be more careful where you tread.  Accidents like that...well...they could be the death of you.&quot;  <br>
<br>
::He then turned and started heading back to one of the trees::<br>
<br>
&quot;But not now...&quot; <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#003366><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=sartha>Sartha</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>registered user</span><br>  Posts: 74<br> <font color=#FFFF33>(6/4/01 3:32 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=24.topic&index=58>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> ::the fight::</span><hr size=1> ::Sartha and the elf continue to fight as two blurs within the night's deadly arms. Finally, Sartha became annoyed with this game they were playing. She stopped dead in her tracks for the only moment that she took until she picked up the sound of the sudden stopping of feet. She chose that moment to spring, sword raised, and impale the elf on her shining rune blade. She made sure the Elf was in as much pain as possible before kneeling close::<br>
<br>
&quot;I want the antidote, or I finish you off...&quot;<br>
<br>
::All that was left was the answer...:: <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#336699><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uxgoddessaphrodite.showPublicProfile?language=EN>xGoddess Aphrodite</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>registered user</span><br>  Posts: 12<br> <font color=#FFFF33>(6/4/01 4:58 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=24.topic&index=59>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: A &quot;lovely&quot; predicament</span><hr size=1> ::Her trip from Athena, which was a long one, might be key to heal the amazon.  After getting permission to heal the warrior she rubs her hand together and places them on the woman.  Aphrodite chants softly, and the healing takes place.  She looks up to find relief that Hades left.  She knows that the amazon will be far from death's arms at this moment in time::<br>
